This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on the mobility and safety of rescue robots. It may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves planning and decision-making for the robot. Computer Vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category as the robot needs to perceive and navigate through 3D terrain. The Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may also be applicable as the paper discusses the control of the robot's flippers. Lastly, the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category may be relevant as the paper may involve learning-based approaches for flipper planning.
